MESSAGE.value: Start to split lexer rules from parser rules and using a visitor.
Remove all generated sources.
Correct visitor compilation error by commenting out unfinished part.
Add a sketch of custom persistence for ANTRL grammar.
Complete build script.
Remove FeatureKind.
Fix the build script.
Add a toText method to convert the grammar back to text. Not as nice as a visitor, but this will do for now to test persistence.
Adjust formatting of text output.
Check for null with safeToText in case the grammar is incomplete and some elements are null.
Introduce safeName and safeValue to handle cases where a text property is not yet defined.
Set name of model on new grammar.
Cleanup the Lexer AST. Make it more similar to the parse tree.
Refactor optional parameters to put them also on lexer atoms.
Fix NPE in LexerElement.
Adjust migration to noit modify itself. Revert effects of a previous modification in migration.
Fix behavior for LexerRuleBlock.
Rename plugin to org.campagnelab.ANTLR.
Add quick fixes and error messages to replace references by name with references to rules (parser or lexer rules).
Support references across roots inside the same model, to enable refs from parser to lexer, when LexerRules are in different files.
Support references across roots inside the same model, to enable refs from parser to lexer, when LexerRules are in different files. Expand visitor to support ebnfBlocks.
Support NotSet e.g., ~[\n\r]
Improve the visitor some more. Still missing a few bits to support the grammar of the R language.
Fix parsing of block. Was incorrectly returning empty alternatives.
Make grammars with no rules valid.

option.value: Make grammars with no rules valid.
